<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-13T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="454" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/6180</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Shea</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-13T17:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your August 4, 5 p.m., August 8, 7 p.m., and August 9, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d454fn1">Telegram of August 8 not printed.</note>
                                You are instructed to seek suitable opportunity to convey, in a
                                discreet manner, to President of Chile, this Government’s due
                                receipt of his friendly expressions and also the information that it
                                is not known when fleet will be in Pacific as its movements are
                                dependent upon many contingencies.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>